A1A.F.summary: Atrium Ljungberg AB (publ) owns, develops, and manages real estate properties primarily in Sweden. The company operates through Properties, and Project and Construction Activities segments. Its property portfolio comprises office premises and retail spaces; house restaurants; residential units; and cultural and educational facilities. The company also undertakes various turnkey contracts and pure construction contract assignments for residential properties and offices. Its property portfolio comprises 67 properties with a total letting area of 1,087,000 square meters in the regions of Stockholm, Gothenburg, MalmÃ¶, and Uppsala. The company was founded in 1946 and is headquartered in Nacka, Sweden.

CAST.ST.summary: Castellum is one of Sweden's largest listed real estate companies with a property value of SEK 98 billion. We are active in 17 Swedish growth regions as well as in Copenhagen and Helsinki. Every day, 250,000 people go to work in our premises. We develop flexible workplaces and logistics solutions in close proximity to city centers and with a lettable area of 4.3 million square meters. One of our sustainability goals is to be completely climate neutral by 2030. Castellum is the only Nordic real estate company selected by the Dow Jones Sustainability Index (DJSI). The Castellum share is listed on the Nasdaq Stockholm Large Cap.

FASTAT.ST.summary: Aktiebolaget Fastator (publ) invests in real estate companies in Sweden. The company owns community service properties, primarily, directly or indirectly, public sector tenants, such as state, municipalities, and regions. It also provides property management services. Aktiebolaget Fastator (publ) was incorporated in 2005 and is headquartered in Stockholm, Sweden.

SIGN-B.ST.summary: Signatur Fastigheter AB (publ) manufactures and sells flame retardant products in Europe. It offers Apyrum flame retardants for industrial and service companies for use in natural and synthetic fibers, PVC, and cellulose-based materials; Apyrum Powder, a fine powder that is added to polymeric materials suspensions where water is not desired; and Apyrum Liquids, a water-based flame retardant that is used for impregnation of natural and mixed fibers and materials. The company was formerly known as Deflamo AB (publ) and changed its name to Signatur Fastigheter AB (publ) in December 2019. Signatur Fastigheter AB (publ) was founded in 2004 and is based in Karlshamn, Sweden.

WAEC.F.summary: Wallenstam AB (publ) develops, builds, sells, and manages residential and commercial properties for people and businesses in Gothenburg and Stockholm, Sweden. Its property portfolio comprises approximately 230 properties, including 10,000 apartments and 1,000 commercial tenants. The company also owns and operates 66 wind turbines with a total combined installed output of 143 megawatts; and engages in solar cells modules business. Wallenstam AB (publ) was founded in 1944 and is headquartered in Gothenburg, Sweden.
